          <li>Long refinement meetings that drain energy</li>
          <li>PBIs that aren't "ready" for sprint planning</li>
          <li>Questions that could have been asked earlier</li>
          <li>Context lost between meetings</li>
          <li>Same mistakes repeated across sprints</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="stat-box" style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
          <div class="number">2-3 hrs</div>
          <div class="label">Average refinement meeting length</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="number">40%</div>
          <div class="label">PBIs rejected at sprint planning</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-number">2 / 17</div>
  </div>

  <!-- Slide 3: Problem Deep Dive -->
  <div class="slide">
    <div class="logo">Backlog Chef</div>
    <h2>Why This Happens</h2>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>No Memory</h3>
        <p>Teams forget past decisions, similar work, and lessons learned. Every refinement starts from scratch.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>No Quality Gate</h3>
        <p>No objective check against Definition of Ready. Incomplete PBIs slip through until sprint planning.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>No Context</h3>
        <p>Missing links to architecture decisions, dependencies, and stakeholder requirements.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top: 60px; text-align: center;">
      <p style="font-size: 28px;">Result: <span class="warn">Wasted time, frustrated teams, lower quality software</span></p>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-number">3 / 17</div>
  </div>

  <!-- Slide 4: Solution -->
  <div class="slide">
    <div class="logo">Backlog Chef</div>
    <h2>The Solution: Backlog Chef</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h3>An AI system that transforms meeting transcripts into high-quality PBIs</h3>
        <ul style="margin-top: 30px;">
          <li><span class="highlight">Automated extraction</span> from meeting transcripts</li>
          <li><span class="highlight">Quality scoring</span> against Definition of Ready</li>
          <li><span class="highlight">Context enrichment</span> from your documentation</li>
          <li><span class="highlight">Smart questions</span> with suggested answers</li>
          <li><span class="highlight">Risk detection</span> before sprint planning</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align: center;">
        <div style="font-size: 120px; margin-bottom: 30px;">üç≥</div>
        <p style="font-size: 20px; color: #94a3b8;">From raw transcript to sprint-ready PBIs</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-number">4 / 17</div>
  </div>

  <!-- Slide 5: How It Works - Pipeline -->
  <div class="slide">
    <div class="logo">Backlog Chef</div>
    <h2>8-Step Intelligence Pipeline</h2>
    <div class="grid-4" style="margin-top: 20px;">
      <div class="pipeline-step">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <h4>Event Detection</h4>
        <p>Identify meeting type</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pipeline-step">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <h4>Extract PBIs</h4>
        <p>Parse candidates from transcript</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pipeline-step">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <h4>Score Quality</h4>
        <p>Evaluate completeness</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pipeline-step">
        <div class="step-num">4</div>
        <h4>Enrich Context</h4>
        <p>Find similar work & docs</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pipeline-step">
        <div class="step-num">5</div>
        <h4>Check Risks</h4>
        <p>Detect dependencies</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pipeline-step">
        <div class="step-num">6</div>
        <h4>Generate Questions</h4>
        <p>Smart Q&A with proposals</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pipeline-step">
        <div class="step-num">7</div>
        <h4>Readiness Check</h4>
        <p>Validate against DoR</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pipeline-step">
        <div class="step-num">8</div>
        <h4>Output</h4>
        <p>Export to your tools</p>
      </div>
    </div>
